  "type": "spell",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"ddb\">\n<p>A hail of rock-hard ice pounds to the ground in a 20-foot-radius, 40-foot-high &amp;Reference[cylinder]{cylinder} centered on a point within range. Each creature in the &amp;Reference[cylinder]{cylinder} must make a &amp;Reference[dex]{Dexterity} saving throw. A creature takes 2d8 &amp;Reference[bludgeoning]{bludgeoning} damage and 4d6 &amp;Reference[cold]{cold} damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>\n<p>Hailstones turn the storm's area of effect into difficult terrain until the end of your next turn.</p>\n<p><em><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong></em> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 5th level or higher, the &amp;Reference[bludgeoning]{bludgeoning} damage increases by 1d8 for each slot level above 4th.</p>\n</div>",
      "chat": ""
    },
